[u'Al Jazeera PR', u'Home', u'About', u'Awards', u'Contact Us', u'Archive', u'Al Jazeera PR', u'\u0647\u0646\u0627 \u0627\u0644\u062c\u0632\u064a\u0631\u0629', u'Search', u'Upfront discusses Obama legacy with Derek Chollet', u'Says those involved with Obama\u2019s Syria policy \u201cdon\u2019t look back\nwith any pride upon what Syria is today\u201d', u'\xa0Says authorizing\nuse of drones was one the most \u201cdifficult issues\u201d Obama\nhad to face', u'Expresses concern over President-elect Donald Trump inheriting\nObama\u2019s military\npowers, including the expanded drone program: \u201cIt\nworries me a lot\u201d', u'Washington, D.C. \u2013 ', u'12', u'th', u', January 2017', u'\xa0- In an interview with Al\nJazeera English\u2019s current affairs show ', u'UpFront', u', Derek Chollet, former\nassistant secretary of defense under\nU.S. President Barack Obama,\nspeaks about the president\u2019s legacy.', u'\xa0\u201cThose of us who were involved in the making\nof Syria policy in the last five years don\u2019t look with any pride upon what\nSyria is today,\u201d Chollet told ', u'UpFront ', u'host Mehdi Hasan.', u'\xa0\u201cThere are many things, as I\u2019ve looked back,\nthat the U.S. could have done differently,\u201d he said.', u'However, Chollet, who wrote\nthe book', u'\u201cI think 1,300 tonnes of chemical weapons out of Syria is good for the world,\ngood for us,\u201d he said.', u'On the subject of the Iran deal, Chollet\ndismissed claims that the president crafted his Syria policies to accommodate the Iranian government and ensure the Iran deal\nremains intact.', u'\u201cI don\u2019t see that, in any way, connected\nto any of the policy decisions on Syria,\u201d he said.', u'During the interview, Chollet was also asked\nabout President Obama\u2019s use of drones.', u'\u201cNo question that the use of drones has been\none of the more controversial and difficult issues that President Obama\u2019s had\nto face,\u201d he said.', u'\u201cHe\u2019s used them quite effectively,\u201d he added.', u'When asked further if he was worried about\nPresident-elect Donald Trump inheriting Obama\u2019s military powers, including the\nexpanded drone program, he replied: \u201cIt worries me a lot.\u201d', u'Note to Editors', u'\xb7\n\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0This \u2018', u'UpFront\u2019', u'th', u'\xb7\n\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0The full show will be available\nthrough this link:', u'\xb7\n\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0If using quotes please credit\nAl Jazeera English and \u2018', u'UpFront\u2019', u'\xb7\n\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0UpFront broadcasts on Fridays\nat 19:30 GMT. Follow \u2018', u'UpFront\u2019', u'@AJUpFront', u'\xb7 \xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0For more\ninformation, or media enquiries, please contact:', u'pressoffice@aljazeera.net', u'derek chollet', u'barack obama', u'al jazeera english', u'al jazeera', u'AlJazeera AJUpFront', u'Mehdi Hasan', u'Read more', u'Facebook', u'Twitter', u'About', u"The Public Relations team at Al Jazeera sharing what's new and exclusive.", u'People I follow', u'Al Jazeera PR', u'Home', u'About', u'Awards', u'Contact Us', u'Archive', u'\xa9 Copyright Al Jazeera 2012\u20132017']